The Senate Tuesday received the report of the Joint Committee on Petroleum (Downstream); Petroleum (Upstream) and Gas Resources on the Petroleum Industry Bill, 2021. The report was laid during plenary by Chairman of the Joint Committee, Senator Sabo Mohammed.President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan, after the report was laid, told lawmakers that the report would be considered on Thursday this week, mandating the Joint Committee to provide lawmakers with copies of the bill ahead of its consideration to enable them study its content. The PIB seeks to establish a framework for the creation of commercially-oriented and profit-driven petroleum entities that ensure value addition and internationalisation of the petroleum industry, promote transparency in the administration of the petroleum resources of Nigeria; and create a conducive business environment for petroleum industry operations.